Appendix D – Electrical and Electronics Architecture Schematics

D.1 Power Distribution Diagram

```
HV Battery (355V) ─┬─ HV Contactors ── Inverter ── Motor
                   └─ HV PTC Heater (4kW)
48V DC/DC (3kW) ── 48V Bus ── Zone Controllers ── Lights, Pumps, Fans
12V DC/DC (300W) ── 12V Bus ── HMI, CAN tranceivers
```

D.2 Zonal Controller Functional Allocation

Zone Controller Loads Communication
Front ZCU‑F Headlamps, DRL, wiper, steering torque sensor, frunk latch, coolant pump CAN FD (chassis)
Rear ZCU‑R Taillamps, charge port lock, inverter enable, reverse lamp CAN FD (powertrain)
Cabin ZCU‑C HVAC blower, PTC relay, seat motors, infotainment display, UI Ethernet (100BASE‑T1)

Ethernet backbone: Single twisted pair, length 5 m, shielded, routed along battery perimeter.

D.3 Battery Management System (BMS) Architecture

· Distributed cell monitoring (10 daisy‑chains, each monitoring 12 cells).
· Master BMS located in battery enclosure.
· Passive balancing (100 mA).
· Contactor control logic:
  · Pre‑charge circuit via 100 Ω resistor.
  · Welding detection algorithm.

Isolation monitoring: Continuous measurement of HV‑to‑chassis resistance; threshold 500 Ω/V.

