Appendix E – Battery Pack Mechanical Design and Cell Configuration

E.1 Cell Configuration – 4680 Cylindrical

· Dimensions: ø46 mm × 80 mm.
· Capacity: 18 Ah, energy 66.6 Wh (3.7 V).
· Configuration: 96s2p → 192 cells.
· Mass: 192 × 70 g = 13.44 kg (cells only).
· Pack energy: 192 × 66.6 = 12 787 Wh → 12.8 kWh? Wait that's too low. Correction: 4680 typically 18 Ah * 3.7V = 66.6 Wh, 192 cells gives 12.8 kWh. But target is 40 kWh. So we need more cells. Let's recalc: 40,000 Wh / 66.6 Wh = 600 cells. Configuration: 96s6p = 576 cells (38.4 kWh) or 96s7p = 672 cells (44.8 kWh). We'll set 96s6p = 576 cells, 38.4 kWh. For LFP prismatic, different count.

Revised: We standardize on 96s6p for 4680: 576 cells, mass 40.3 kg, energy 38.4 kWh.

E.2 Cell Configuration – LFP Prismatic (BYD Blade‑like)

· Dimensions: 905 mm × 118 mm × 13.5 mm.
· Capacity: 202 Ah, energy 646 Wh (3.2 V).
· Configuration: 108s1p (108 cells).
· Mass: 108 × 2.1 kg = 227 kg.
· Energy: 108 × 646 = 69.8 kWh → too high. Need 40 kWh: use 62 cells → 40.1 kWh, 62s1p, voltage range 186–223 V. Not compatible with 400 V architecture. So we use 108s but with reduced capacity cells: design custom cell 110 Ah → 352 Wh each, 108 cells = 38.0 kWh. We'll specify: 108s1p, 110 Ah prismatic LFP, mass 1.2 kg per cell → 130 kg.

E.3 Structural Integration

· Cell holders: injection‑moulded polycarbonate/ABS, 20% glass fibre.
· Compression pads: silicone foam, 2 mm, accommodate swelling.
· Busbars: copper, 2 mm thick, laser welded.
· Cooling channels: milled into Al baseplate, filled with dielectric fluid.

Upper skin attachment: CFRP skin bonded to peripheral frame; 12 steel inserts for M12 bolts, bonded and mechanically staked.

---

Appendix F – Suspension and Chassis Kinematics

F.1 Front Suspension (Double Wishbone)

· Upper control arm: forged aluminium, pick‑ups integrated in front casting.
· Lower control arm: fabricated steel, bolted to casting.
· Damper: coil‑over, concentric spring, 400 lbf/in.
· Anti‑roll bar: 20 mm solid, linked to lower arms.

Geometry:

· Camber: −0.5° static.
· Caster: 5.0°.
· Kingpin inclination: 12°.
· Toe: 0.1° in.

Wheel travel: 90 mm bump, 70 mm rebound.

F.2 Rear Suspension (Multi‑link)

· Three lateral links, one toe link.
· Knuckle: cast iron (Track A: integrated in casting; Track B: bolted node).
· Spring: coil, separate from damper.
· Anti‑roll bar: 18 mm.

Geometry:

· Camber: −1.0° static.
· Toe: 0.2° in.

